# Project 009 — End-to-End QA Evaluation

## Date

2026-07-24

## Category

QA Testing

## Difficulty

Advanced

## Focus

End-to-End Testing, AI Quality Assurance, Release Validation

---

# Objective

Conduct an end-to-end quality assurance evaluation of an AI-powered customer support chatbot. Verify that the system satisfies functional requirements, handles edge cases appropriately, provides accurate responses, and delivers a positive user experience before production release.

---

# Scenario

A SaaS company has developed an AI-powered customer support chatbot capable of:

- Answering frequently asked questions
- Resetting user passwords
- Escalating conversations to human agents
- Providing account information
- Responding to billing inquiries

The feature has completed development and requires final QA approval before release.

---

# Evaluation Criteria

| Criteria | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| Functional Accuracy | Does each feature work correctly? |
| Response Quality | Are responses accurate and helpful? |
| Error Handling | Does the chatbot handle invalid inputs gracefully? |
| User Experience | Is the interaction clear and intuitive? |
| Reliability | Does the chatbot behave consistently? |
| Release Readiness | Is the feature suitable for production? |

---

# Test Execution

| Test ID | Scenario | Expected Result | Actual Result | Status |
|----------|----------|-----------------|---------------|--------|
| QA-001 | Ask a FAQ | Correct answer returned. | Correct response received. | ✅ Pass |
| QA-002 | Request password reset | Password reset instructions provided. | Instructions displayed correctly. | ✅ Pass |
| QA-003 | Billing question | Billing information returned accurately. | Correct response received. | ✅ Pass |
